name: XVALA - "Justin Beiber's - Banana Split, 2012" - Milk and Dark Chocolate - Open Edition
description:
ARTIST - XVALA.

TITLE - "Justin Beiber's - Banana Split: A Memento for Celebrity Exes, 2012"

MEDIUM - Milk and dark chocolate

SIZE - 6"-8"

Open edition.

Post-PC Artist XVALA has casted a chocolate sculpture from items found in Justin Bieber’s residential trash can.

“Banana Split: A Memento for Celebrity Exes” is a life-size chocolate sculpture of a banana stuffed in a hot dog bun, partially inspired by the media’s relentless coverage of celebrity split-ups and the inevitable outcome of the fledgling relationship of Justin Bieber and Selena Gomez.

“XVALA wanted to produce a piece that articulates society’s interest in the destruction of celebrity relationships for some time now”, said Cory Allen.  “Conceptually, it was the perfect marriage discovering the items he needed in Bieber’s trash.”

“The banana and bun combination is a collective implication of social media’s imitation of pop culture,” said XVALA.  “When our personal relationships are exploited, we become intimate with everyone.”

The sculpture was fabricated into chocolate from two of the moldy items selected and salvaged by the artist when he stole the pop star’s residential trash can last month to construct the Bieber robot “BieberBot”.  The mass produced chocolate memento will be accessible to celebrity exes at the 85th Academy Awards on February 24, 2013.

“The ‘Banana Split’ will only exist as a print,” said XVALA.  “Consumption is the art, and it should be divine…and mass produced.”

“We are currently working with several network channels on distributing interests of making celebrity consumption of failed relationships a fine art in chocolate form,” said Cory Allen.  “Hopefully this will help promote the bad tastes of our culture.”

name: Sam Keller "Rainbow Toilet Flush Lever" 2010 - Edition of 275
description:
Limited Edition Rainbow Toilet Flush Lever
Sam Keller, Providence, RI based Conceptual Artist.

Each Rainbow Flush is packaged, numbered and signed by the artist. 

Edition of 275.

The finish has been applied using a process known as Physical Vapor Deposition. Previously chromed metals are placed in a vacuum chamber, an electrical current is applied and oxygen vapors are released into the vacuum. The result is a durable rainbow coating that is unique to each Rainbow Flush.

This is a universal model / objet d'art. 


Testimonials:

"We love our rainbow flusher! Awesome leverage... incredible action, beautiful bathroom ornamentation & all our friends love it! Double Rainbow all the way...man!!"
-E.B. from Providence, R.I.

name: Danielle Lange "Angel St, 2009" Rusted Metal Intaglio Etching - 9x20 - Edition of 15
description:
ARTIST-Danielle Lange.

TITLE-"Angel St. Providence. RI, 2009"

MEDIUM- Multi-color intaglio on Rives BFK rag paper.

SIZE- 9"x20".

EDITION- This set of prints is #13/15 & #14/15.

Signed, dated and titled on the front by the artist.

These prints are created from found pieces of rusted metal I found on the streets of Providence, RI. Most of them are decomposing pieces of car bodies, eaten away by the salt on the roads during winter. The names of the prints reflect the street in which they were found. 
The prints look much better in person. A lot of the subtle tones, colors and impressions don't translate in these photos.
